<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1873-06-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1873-06-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="174" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d174">
                        <head>No. 480.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName corresp="#p_GHH1" type="from">Heap</persName> to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_WH1" type="to">Hunter</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Consulate
                                        of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Tunis</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1873-06-11"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 11, 1873</date>.
                                (Received July 9.)</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 150.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Bey has notified me officially in
                            writing that the four persons apprehended for the murder of Mahmood
                            Sennen, dragoman of the United States consular agent at Bizerta, have
                            been tried and sentenced.</p>
                        <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><persName corresp="#p_GHH1">G. H. HEAP</persName>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>